reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fabulous! Sturdy little folding table. GREAT DESIGN.
reviews.reviewText: I have been looking for a small narrow table like this for over a year to use in a remodeled dressing area to do my hair & makeup. I build a lot of Ikea and other types of furniture and this was a breeze. Great design, simple. And it folds up! Who Knew? There's a nice little " Z " bar that attaches to the side, so I hung my hairdryer. I love the white legs. Metal spray painted legs. The top is a faux wood in a very light birtch color. I am blown away by the quality and excellent design. This little desk can be used for anything and nice enough to go into any space. Just a great looking, highly functional and well made peice of furniture.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really Useful MiniDesk
reviews.reviewText: This desk is easy to assemble. It is a great size for my computer or craft projects. I love this desk because you can fold it up and easily move it but it also has some weight so it is stable and solid. This is my second mini desk. I used the first one for taking photos for my jewelry business. This one I hope to use for various craft and art projects for my garden. Great price, easy to set up, easy to move around or fold up and store. Super useful!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great, sturdy desk with good space
reviews.reviewText: Love this desk. I needed a portable desk to set up for digital archiving. This desk is excellent. It is easy to set up. Looks great, is stable over different surfaces. I can fit my laptop, scanner and docs all in the space. It stores easily and slides away behind my couch.So happy with this purchase. Easy to put together, good instructions. Would purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent desk for WFH
reviews.reviewText: I needed a desk for a small space that I could put away when not in use, and this has fit the bill well. It was very easy to set up, and easily fold/unfolds when I need it to. It’s small, but has plenty of room for everything I need. It would work well for someone who works from home occasionally as it has room for a laptop, mousepad, and a little extra for a notebook and maybe a coffee mug. Folded, it fits easily in a narrow space between my couch and end table. My only complaint is that the legs don’t seem to be QUITE level, and one sort of floats while the other touches the ground, but it hasn’t affected its functioning so it’s not too big of a deal to me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this desk!
reviews.reviewText: I needed something that I could use for my diamond painting and Lego building that could easily be stored when not in use and let me tell you this desk is perfect! Super sturdy and I love that the legs snap in when it is set up. Just the right height so I am not hunched over while working. Also really easy to assemble and looks really nice. Would 10/10 recommend!

reviews.reviewText: Took less than 20 min to assemble even without a good place to lay it out in. Would have been quicker with moe spce. Definitely recommend.
